[4]
Date: Fri, 22 Nov 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Dutch Ministry of Agriculture, Nature Management and Fisheries,
Press Release 22 Nov 2002 [translated and edited]
<http://www.minlnv.nl/infomart/persinfo/>

A BSE case in Boekel
--------------------
A case of BSE has been recorded in a cow 4.5 years old in a farm in Boekel
(North Brabant).
This is the 51th case of BSE in the Netherlands since 1997, and the 23rd
during 2002.
The cow, "Sientje 54", born on 1 Feb 1998, has been forwarded by the owner
for incineration on 12 Nov 2002. The rapid BSE-test was found positive on
16 Nov 2002, followed by a confirmatory test which has become positive on
21 Nov 2002.
There have been no suspicious clinical signs in any of the other 72 bovines
on the farm. "Sientje 54" was born and reared on the same farm in Boekel. .
As usual, an investigation into the feed will be carried out, with special
reference to the feed consumed during the first months of the [life of
the?] affected cow. The cows on the farm have been evacuated [destroyed?].
The same will be done with all animals from the said farm that have reached
other farms.
[During the whole of 2001, 20 BSE cases have been recorded in the
Netherlands, compared to 23 during the first 10.5 months of 2002. - Mod AS]
